args: (I'm just a shadow of Eirene's old partner.)
(And all this time, whenever Eirene looked\nat me, I bet all she saw was the old Finni.)
Even her promise to stay at my side until\nthe day of our destruction was probably\nmeant for the android I once was.
That leaves me with only one option...
I must BECOME her—the ＂me＂ who\ninhabited this heart a thousand years ago!
The trouble is, I can't personally\nrewrite my own circuits.
I guess I'll start with the superficial stuff.\nFirst, I'll work on copying her fighting style!
Perfect timing, fiend! I'll finish you\noff using her patented counter style.\nCome at me!
Hngh! That smarts, but now it's time for me\nto give you a taste of your own medicine.\nHraaah!
Tenacious little bastard, aren't you? Wait...\nAm I operating at a lower output because I\ntook those attacks head-on?!
Rgh. I totally failed to mimic her combat\nstyle. Gotta think of a different approach!
There's no point in blindly imitating her\nform. I guess it's what's on the inside that\nmatters most after all.
Meaning I should try to THINK like her, not\njust move like her. She didn't go charging\nin half-cocked; she was more analytical.
C'mon, Finni, think! How would she\ndeal with an opponent of this size?
Assess like an android, logically...\nAim for minimum losses with\nmaximum efficiency...
I know. I'll aim for the enemy's legs to\nimpede its movement with the least effort.\nNow, time to put the plan into—huh?
Dammit! I got too wrapped up in planning,\nand now the enemy's right in my face.\nGotta brace for impact!
▷We came to make sure you were okay.◁\nWarning. This is a disadvantageous\nsituation. I advise that you withdraw.

Your abnormal behavior since the other
day has intensified. I assess that it will be
difficult for you to participate in combat
at your current performance level.
Urgh... I'm not being ＂abnormal＂! I could\npound that thing into a fine paste in less\nthan a microsecond if I felt like it!
Because I've already made up my mind to\nbecome HER, and that means I can't act\nin a way that she wouldn't now!
Evidence of abnormality confirmed.\nContinued combat operations will prove\nstrenuous. We should withdraw.
▷I agree with Laxi. Come back with us\nand tell us what's on your mind, Finni.◁
▷You're attempting to become the Finni\nthat Eirene tried to bring back a thousand\nyears ago?◁
▷Do you understand what that actually\nmeans? You're putting your life on the line\nto be someone you're not!◁
I'm doing no such thing. I'm only\ntrying to be diligent and mimic her.

I mean, sure, maybe jumping right into a
real combat situation wasn't a good idea.
I usually just go with the flow when I'm
fighting, so I got stuck in my head.
If we had arrived any later, you\nwould be in the scrap pile by now.
Gee, you've only reminded me at least a\nthousand times by now! ANYWAY... It's\nclear I'm going about this the wrong way.
I can't make Eirene happy like this. If\nanything, I'll end up a thorn in her side.
For her sake, I need to do this right.\nI'm talking making precise adjustments to\nbetter reflect the old Finni's combat style.
Instead of copying her, I'll carefully\nanalyze the memories I've restored and\nmake my body adapt to them.
▷Finni, do you REALLY think this\nis going to make Eirene happy...?◁
It will. It has to. Otherwise, how\ncould I justify even being here?
For this, you endure and then input\ncalculation time... Ah. And here, you wait\nfor the enemy to move and THEN counter...
Finni's muttering to herself again.\nShe's always like this as of late.

In this scenario, there's a 98% chance that
she would refrain from interfering. Taking
into consideration the previous incident,
the reason for that is... *mumble*
What in the world is going on with her?\nShould I be worried...?
